  "texts": [
    "To generate a training dataset, first we sample a vector x (1×n) ∼ N (0, 1) and add perturbations δ (d×n) ∼ N (0, α 2) to it, resulting in X (d×n) train = x (1×n) + δ (d×n).",
    "The α controls the level of correlation in the input features.",
    "A low α indicates a high correlation among the input features and vice versa.",
    "After that, we sample ϵ (1×n) ∼ N (0, σ 2) and create Y (1×n) train = w (1×d) X (d×n) train + ϵ (1×n).",
    "We sample another x (1×n) and repeat the process for the test dataset."
  ],
